---
title: Next.js
name: Next.js
description: Send email from a Next.js Server Action with the top-level mail().
category: Frameworks
---

Postboi is framework-agnostic â€” read the request's `FormData` in a Server Action and hand it
straight to [`mail()`](/api). Postboi extracts the [special fields](/formdata#special-fields)
and renders the rest into a tidy HTML table.

```tsx
// app/actions.ts
'use server'
import { mail } from 'postboi'

export async function submit(_prev: unknown, body: FormData) {
	await mail({ body })
	return { ok: true }
}
```

Point a client-component form at it. Include hidden `_subject` and `_reply_to` fields, and
mirror the visitor's email into `_reply_to` (with `useState`) so replying reaches the sender:

```tsx
// app/page.tsx
'use client'
import { useActionState, useState } from 'react'
import { submit } from './actions'

export default function Page() {
	const [email, setEmail] = useState('')
	const [state, action] = useActionState(submit, null)

	return (
		<form action={action}>
			<input type="hidden" name="_subject" value="Contact Form" />
			<input type="hidden" name="_reply_to" value={email} />
			<input name="contactâ†’name" placeholder="Name" required />
			<input
				name="contactâ†’email"
				type="email"
				value={email}
				onChange={(e) => setEmail(e.target.value)}
				required
			/>
			<textarea name="detailsâ†’message" placeholder="Message" />
			<button type="submit">Send</button>
		</form>
	)
}
```

Field names use the [`fieldsetâ†’field`](/formdata#grouped-fields) syntax. The provider and
default recipient come from [`postboi.config.ts`](/config) â€” a `POSTBOI_TOKEN` routes to
[Postboi Cloud](/cloud), or pick any [provider](/providers).

## Or use the MailForm component

`postboi/react` ships the form boilerplate as a component â€” the [spam-protection](/spam)
honeypot, hidden special fields from props, and (given your dashboard's `captcha` key)
the managed invisible captcha:

```tsx
'use client'
import { useActionState, useState } from 'react'
import { MailForm } from 'postboi/react'
import { submit } from './actions'

export default function Page() {
	const [email, setEmail] = useState('')
	const [, action] = useActionState(submit, null)

	return (
		<MailForm action={action} subject="Contact Form" reply_to={email} captcha="pk_â€¦">
			<input name="contactâ†’name" placeholder="Name" required />
			<input
				name="contactâ†’email"
				type="email"
				value={email}
				onChange={(e) => setEmail(e.target.value)}
				required
			/>
			<textarea name="detailsâ†’message" placeholder="Message" />
			<button type="submit">Send</button>
		</MailForm>
	)
}
```

See [Spam protection](/spam#form-components) for every prop.

**Runnable example:** [`examples/nextjs-provider-postboi`](https://github.com/darbymanning/postboi/tree/main/examples/nextjs-provider-postboi).
